by chalasr at 2016-05-03T15:35:43Z

@fabpot As we (developers) are always looking for a faster install/update of project dependencies, I really don't think that people take care of these suggestions during the composer processes execution itself.
Personally, it's something that I see only after that (from my IDE, or directly on packagist).

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

by stof at 2016-05-03T15:55:15Z

> I was curious because I think that the way suggest are displayed (only during composer install or update) is not that useful

@fabpot  that's not true anymore. Composer has a command allowing you to see suggestions from installed packages at any time: ``composer suggests`` (more useful in verbose mode)

